5600 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_UNDEF(SDNode *N) {
5601  EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
5602  return DAG.getUNDEF(WidenVT);
5603 }
5604 
5605 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_VECTOR_SHUFFLE(ShuffleVectorSDNode *N) {
5606  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5607  SDLoc dl(N);
5608 
5609  EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
5610  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
5611  unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
5612 
5613  SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
5614  SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
5615 
5616  // Adjust mask based on new input vector length.
5617  SmallVector<int, 16> NewMask;
5618  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
5619  int Idx = N->getMaskElt(i);
5620  if (Idx < (int)NumElts)
5621  NewMask.push_back(Idx);
5622  else
5623  NewMask.push_back(Idx - NumElts + WidenNumElts);
5624  }
5625  for (unsigned i = NumElts; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
5626  NewMask.push_back(-1);
5627  return DAG.getVectorShuffle(WidenVT, dl, InOp1, InOp2, NewMask);
5628 }
5629 
5630 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_VECTOR_REVERSE(SDNode *N) {
5631  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5632  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
5633  SDLoc dl(N);
5634 
5635  EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
5636  SDValue OpValue = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
5637  assert(WidenVT == OpValue.getValueType() && "Unexpected widened vector type");
5638 
5639  SDValue ReverseVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE, dl, WidenVT, OpValue);
5640  unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
5641  unsigned VTNumElts = VT.getVectorMinNumElements();
5642  unsigned IdxVal = WidenNumElts - VTNumElts;
5643 
5644  if (VT.isScalableVector()) {
5645  // Try to split the 'Widen ReverseVal' into smaller extracts and concat the
5646  // results together, e.g.(nxv6i64 -> nxv8i64)
5647  // nxv8i64 vector_reverse
5648  // <->
5649  // nxv8i64 concat(
5650  // nxv2i64 extract_subvector(nxv8i64, 2)
5651  // nxv2i64 extract_subvector(nxv8i64, 4)
5652  // nxv2i64 extract_subvector(nxv8i64, 6)
5653  // nxv2i64 undef)
5654 
5655  unsigned GCD = std::gcd(VTNumElts, WidenNumElts);
5656  EVT PartVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT,
5657  ElementCount::getScalable(GCD));
5658  assert((IdxVal % GCD) == 0 && "Expected Idx to be a multiple of the broken "
5659  "down type's element count");
5660  SmallVector<SDValue> Parts;
5661  unsigned i = 0;
5662  for (; i < VTNumElts / GCD; ++i)
5663  Parts.push_back(
5664  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, PartVT, ReverseVal,
5665  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(IdxVal + i * GCD, dl)));
5666  for (; i < WidenNumElts / GCD; ++i)
5667  Parts.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(PartVT));
5668 
5669  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, Parts);
5670  }
5671 
5672  // Use VECTOR_SHUFFLE to combine new vector from 'ReverseVal' for
5673  // fixed-vectors.
5674  SmallVector<int, 16> Mask;
5675  for (unsigned i = 0; i != VTNumElts; ++i) {
5676  Mask.push_back(IdxVal + i);
5677  }
5678  for (unsigned i = VTNumElts; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
5679  Mask.push_back(-1);
5680 
5681  return DAG.getVectorShuffle(WidenVT, dl, ReverseVal, DAG.getUNDEF(WidenVT),
5682  Mask);
5683 }
5684 
5685 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
5686  assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
5687  N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
5688  "Operands must be vectors");
5689  EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
5690  ElementCount WidenEC = WidenVT.getVectorElementCount();
5691 
5692  SDValue InOp1 = N->getOperand(0);
5693  EVT InVT = InOp1.getValueType();
5694  assert(InVT.isVector() && "can not widen non-vector type");
5695  EVT WidenInVT =
5696  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), InVT.getVectorElementType(), WidenEC);
5697 
5698  // The input and output types often differ here, and it could be that while
5699  // we'd prefer to widen the result type, the input operands have been split.
5700  // In this case, we also need to split the result of this node as well.
5701  if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector) {
5702  SDValue SplitVSetCC = SplitVecOp_VSETCC(N);
5703  SDValue Res = ModifyToType(SplitVSetCC, WidenVT);
5704  return Res;
5705  }
5706 
5707  // If the inputs also widen, handle them directly. Otherwise widen by hand.
5708  SDValue InOp2 = N->getOperand(1);
5709  if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector) {
5710  InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(InOp1);
5711  InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(InOp2);
5712  } else {
5713  InOp1 = DAG.WidenVector(InOp1, SDLoc(N));
5714  InOp2 = DAG.WidenVector(InOp2, SDLoc(N));
5715  }
5716 
5717  // Assume that the input and output will be widen appropriately. If not,
5718  // we will have to unroll it at some point.
5719  assert(InOp1.getValueType() == WidenInVT &&
5720  InOp2.getValueType() == WidenInVT &&
5721  "Input not widened to expected type!");
5722  (void)WidenInVT;
5723  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::VP_SETCC) {
5724  SDValue Mask =
5725  GetWidenedMask(N->getOperand(3), WidenVT.getVectorElementCount());
5726  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SETCC, SDLoc(N), WidenVT, InOp1, InOp2,
5727  N->getOperand(2), Mask, N->getOperand(4));
5728  }
5729  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, SDLoc(N), WidenVT, InOp1, InOp2,
5730  N->getOperand(2));
5731 }
5732 
5733 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_STRICT_FSETCC(SDNode *N) {
5734  assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
5735  N->getOperand(1).getValueType().isVector() &&
5736  "Operands must be vectors");
5737  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5738  EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
5739  unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
5740  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
5741  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
5742 
5743  SDLoc dl(N);
5744  SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
5745  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(1);
5746  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(2);
5747  SDValue CC = N->getOperand(3);
5748  EVT TmpEltVT = LHS.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
5749 
5750  // Fully unroll and reassemble.
5751  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars(WidenNumElts, DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
5752  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Chains(NumElts);
5753  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
5754  SDValue LHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, LHS,
5755  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
5756  SDValue RHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, RHS,
5757  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
5758 
5759  Scalars[i] = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, {MVT::i1, MVT::Other},
5760  {Chain, LHSElem, RHSElem, CC});
5761  Chains[i] = Scalars[i].getValue(1);
5762  Scalars[i] = DAG.getSelect(dl, EltVT, Scalars[i],
5763  DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, EltVT, VT),
5764  DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, EltVT, VT));
5765  }
5766 
5767  SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Chains);
5768  ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
5769 
5770  return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Scalars);
5771 }
5772 
5773 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5774 // Widen Vector Operand
5775 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5776 bool DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVectorOperand(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
5777  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Widen node operand " << OpNo << ": "; N->dump(&DAG);
5778  dbgs() << "\n");
5779  SDValue Res = SDValue();
5780 
5781  // See if the target wants to custom widen this node.
5782  if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType(), false))
5783  return false;
5784 
5785  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
5786  default:
5787 #ifndef NDEBUG
5788  dbgs() << "WidenVectorOperand op #" << OpNo << ": ";
5789  N->dump(&DAG);
5790  dbgs() << "\n";
5791 #endif
5792  llvm_unreachable("Do not know how to widen this operator's operand!");
5793 
5794  case ISD::BITCAST: Res = WidenVecOp_BITCAST(N); break;
5795  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: Res = WidenVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(N); break;
5796  case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: Res = WidenVecOp_INSERT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
5797  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: Res = WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
5798  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: Res = WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
5799  case ISD::STORE: Res = WidenVecOp_STORE(N); break;
5800  case ISD::VP_STORE: Res = WidenVecOp_VP_STORE(N, OpNo); break;
5801  case ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_STORE:
5802  Res = WidenVecOp_VP_STRIDED_STORE(N, OpNo);
5803  break;
5804  case ISD::MSTORE: Res = WidenVecOp_MSTORE(N, OpNo); break;
5805  case ISD::MGATHER: Res = WidenVecOp_MGATHER(N, OpNo); break;
5806  case ISD::MSCATTER: Res = WidenVecOp_MSCATTER(N, OpNo); break;
5807  case ISD::VP_SCATTER: Res = WidenVecOp_VP_SCATTER(N, OpNo); break;
5808  case ISD::SETCC: Res = WidenVecOp_SETCC(N); break;
5809  case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
5810  case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS: Res = WidenVecOp_STRICT_FSETCC(N); break;
5811  case ISD::VSELECT: Res = WidenVecOp_VSELECT(N); break;
5812  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: Res = WidenVecOp_FCOPYSIGN(N); break;
5813  case ISD::IS_FPCLASS: Res = WidenVecOp_IS_FPCLASS(N); break;
5814 
5815  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
5816  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
5817  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
5818  Res = WidenVecOp_EXTEND(N);
5819  break;
5820 
5821  case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
5822  case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:
5823  case ISD::FP_ROUND:
5824  case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
5825  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
5826  case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT:
5827  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
5828  case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT:
5829  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
5830  case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP:
5831  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
5832  case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP:
5833  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
5834  Res = WidenVecOp_Convert(N);
5835  break;
5836 
5837  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
5838  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
5839  Res = WidenVecOp_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(N);
5840  break;
5841 
5842  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
5843  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL:
5844  case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
5845  case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
5846  case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
5847  case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
5848  case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
5849  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
5850  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
5851  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
5852  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
5853  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
5854  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
5855  Res = WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE(N);
5856  break;
5857  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
5858  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
5859  Res = WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE_SEQ(N);
5860  break;
5861  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FADD:
5862  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
5863  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMUL:
5864  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
5865  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_ADD:
5866  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_MUL:
5867  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND:
5868  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR:
5869  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR:
5870  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMAX:
5871  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMIN:
5872  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMAX:
5873  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMIN:
5874  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMAX:
5875  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMIN:
5876  Res = WidenVecOp_VP_REDUCE(N);
5877  break;
5878  }
5879 
5880  // If Res is null, the sub-method took care of registering the result.
5881  if (!Res.getNode()) return false;
5882 
5883  // If the result is N, the sub-method updated N in place. Tell the legalizer
5884  // core about this.
5885  if (Res.getNode() == N)
5886  return true;
5887 
5888 
5889  if (N->isStrictFPOpcode())
5890  assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 2 &&
5891  "Invalid operand expansion");
5892  else
5893  assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 1 &&
5894  "Invalid operand expansion");
5895 
5896  ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
5897  return false;
5898 }
5899 
5900 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_EXTEND(SDNode *N) {
5901  SDLoc DL(N);
5902  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5903 
5904  SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
5905  assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
5906  TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
5907  "Unexpected type action");
5908  InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
5909  assert(VT.getVectorNumElements() <
5910  InOp.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() &&
5911  "Input wasn't widened!");
5912 
5913  // We may need to further widen the operand until it has the same total
5914  // vector size as the result.
5915  EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
5916  if (InVT.getSizeInBits() != VT.getSizeInBits()) {
5917  EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
5918  for (EVT FixedVT : MVT::vector_valuetypes()) {
5919  EVT FixedEltVT = FixedVT.getVectorElementType();
5920  if (TLI.isTypeLegal(FixedVT) &&
5921  FixedVT.getSizeInBits() == VT.getSizeInBits() &&
5922  FixedEltVT == InEltVT) {
5923  assert(FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() >= VT.getVectorNumElements() &&
5924  "Not enough elements in the fixed type for the operand!");
5925  assert(FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() != InVT.getVectorNumElements() &&
5926  "We can't have the same type as we started with!");
5927  if (FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() > InVT.getVectorNumElements())
5928  InOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, FixedVT,
5929  DAG.getUNDEF(FixedVT), InOp,
5930  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
5931  else
5932  InOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, FixedVT, InOp,
5933  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
5934  break;
5935  }
5936  }
5937  InVT = InOp.getValueType();
5938  if (InVT.getSizeInBits() != VT.getSizeInBits())
5939  // We couldn't find a legal vector type that was a widening of the input
5940  // and could be extended in-register to the result type, so we have to
5941  // scalarize.
5942  return WidenVecOp_Convert(N);
5943  }
5944 
5945  // Use special DAG nodes to represent the operation of extending the
5946  // low lanes.
5947  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
5948  default:
5949  llvm_unreachable("Extend legalization on extend operation!");
5950  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
5951  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
5952  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
5953  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
5954  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
5955  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
5956  }
5957 }
5958 
5959 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_FCOPYSIGN(SDNode *N) {
5960  // The result (and first input) is legal, but the second input is illegal.
5961  // We can't do much to fix that, so just unroll and let the extracts off of
5962  // the second input be widened as needed later.
5963  return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N);
5964 }
5965 
5966 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_IS_FPCLASS(SDNode *N) {
5967  SDLoc DL(N);
5968  EVT ResultVT = N->getValueType(0);
5969  SDValue Test = N->getOperand(1);
5970  SDValue WideArg = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
5971 
5972  // Process this node similarly to SETCC.
5973  EVT WideResultVT = getSetCCResultType(WideArg.getValueType());
5974  if (ResultVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
5975  WideResultVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i1,
5976  WideResultVT.getVectorNumElements());
5977 
5978  SDValue WideNode = DAG.getNode(ISD::IS_FPCLASS, DL, WideResultVT,
5979  {WideArg, Test}, N->getFlags());
5980 
5981  // Extract the needed results from the result vector.
5982  EVT ResVT =
5983  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WideResultVT.getVectorElementType(),
5984  ResultVT.getVectorNumElements());
5985  SDValue CC = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, ResVT, WideNode,
5986  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
5987 
5988  EVT OpVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
5989  ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
5990  TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT));
5991  return DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, DL, ResultVT, CC);
5992 }
5993 
5994 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_Convert(SDNode *N) {
5995  // Since the result is legal and the input is illegal.
5996  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5997  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
5998  SDLoc dl(N);
5999  SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0);
6000  assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
6001  TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6002  "Unexpected type action");
6003  InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
6004  EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
6005  unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
6006 
6007  // See if a widened result type would be legal, if so widen the node.
6008  // FIXME: This isn't safe for StrictFP. Other optimization here is needed.
6009  EVT WideVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT,
6010  InVT.getVectorElementCount());
6011  if (TLI.isTypeLegal(WideVT) && !N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
6012  SDValue Res;
6013  if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
6014  if (Opcode == ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND)
6015  Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { WideVT, MVT::Other },
6016  { N->getOperand(0), InOp, N->getOperand(2) });
6017  else
6018  Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { WideVT, MVT::Other },
6019  { N->getOperand(0), InOp });
6020  // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
6021  // use the new one.
6022  ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
6023  } else {
6024  if (Opcode == ISD::FP_ROUND)
6025  Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, WideVT, InOp, N->getOperand(1));
6026  else
6027  Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, WideVT, InOp);
6028  }
6029  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, Res,
6030  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
6031  }
6032 
6033  EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
6034 
6035  // Unroll the convert into some scalar code and create a nasty build vector.
6036  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
6037  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumElts);
6038  if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
6039  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> NewOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
6040  SmallVector<SDValue, 32> OpChains;
6041  for (unsigned i=0; i < NumElts; ++i) {
6042  NewOps[1] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, InEltVT, InOp,
6043  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
6044  Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { EltVT, MVT::Other }, NewOps);
6045  OpChains.push_back(Ops[i].getValue(1));
6046  }
6047  SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, OpChains);
6048  ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
6049  } else {
6050  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i)
6051  Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, EltVT,
6052  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, InEltVT,
6053  InOp, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl)));
6054  }
6055 
6056  return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Ops);
6057 }
6058 
6059 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(SDNode *N) {
6060  EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0);
6061  SDValue Src = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6062  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
6063  ElementCount WideNumElts = SrcVT.getVectorElementCount();
6064  SDLoc dl(N);
6065 
6066  // See if a widened result type would be legal, if so widen the node.
6067  EVT WideDstVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6068  DstVT.getVectorElementType(), WideNumElts);
6069  if (TLI.isTypeLegal(WideDstVT)) {
6070  SDValue Res =
6071  DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, WideDstVT, Src, N->getOperand(1));
6072  return DAG.getNode(
6073  ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, DstVT, Res,
6074  DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
6075  }
6076 
6077  // Give up and unroll.
6078  return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N);
6079 }
6080 
6081 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {
6082  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6083  SDValue InOp = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6084  EVT InWidenVT = InOp.getValueType();
6085  SDLoc dl(N);
6086 
6087  // Check if we can convert between two legal vector types and extract.
6088  TypeSize InWidenSize = InWidenVT.getSizeInBits();
6089  TypeSize Size = VT.getSizeInBits();
6090  // x86mmx is not an acceptable vector element type, so don't try.
6091  if (!VT.isVector() && VT != MVT::x86mmx &&
6092  InWidenSize.hasKnownScalarFactor(Size)) {
6093  unsigned NewNumElts = InWidenSize.getKnownScalarFactor(Size);
6094  EVT NewVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT, NewNumElts);
6095  if (TLI.isTypeLegal(NewVT)) {
6096  SDValue BitOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, InOp);
6097  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, VT, BitOp,
6098  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
6099  }
6100  }
6101 
6102  // Handle a case like bitcast v12i8 -> v3i32. Normally that would get widened
6103  // to v16i8 -> v4i32, but for a target where v3i32 is legal but v12i8 is not,
6104  // we end up here. Handling the case here with EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR avoids
6105  // having to copy via memory.
6106  if (VT.isVector()) {
6107  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
6108  unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
6109  if (InWidenSize.isKnownMultipleOf(EltSize)) {
6110  ElementCount NewNumElts =
6111  (InWidenVT.getVectorElementCount() * InWidenVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
6112  .divideCoefficientBy(EltSize);
6113  EVT NewVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT, NewNumElts);
6114  if (TLI.isTypeLegal(NewVT)) {
6115  SDValue BitOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, InOp);
6116  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, BitOp,
6117  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
6118  }
6119  }
6120  }
6121 
6122  return CreateStackStoreLoad(InOp, VT);
6123 }
6124 
6125 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(SDNode *N) {
6126  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6127  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
6128  EVT InVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
6129  SDLoc dl(N);
6130 
6131  // If the widen width for this operand is the same as the width of the concat
6132  // and all but the first operand is undef, just use the widened operand.
6133  unsigned NumOperands = N->getNumOperands();
6134  if (VT == TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), InVT)) {
6135  unsigned i;
6136  for (i = 1; i < NumOperands; ++i)
6137  if (!N->getOperand(i).isUndef())
6138  break;
6139 
6140  if (i == NumOperands)
6141  return GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6142  }
6143 
6144  // Otherwise, fall back to a nasty build vector.
6145  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
6146  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumElts);
6147 
6148  unsigned NumInElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
6149 
6150  unsigned Idx = 0;
6151  for (unsigned i=0; i < NumOperands; ++i) {
6152  SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(i);
6153  assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
6154  TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6155  "Unexpected type action");
6156  InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
6157  for (unsigned j = 0; j < NumInElts; ++j)
6158  Ops[Idx++] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
6159  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(j, dl));
6160  }
6161  return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Ops);
6162 }
6163 
6164 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_INSERT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N) {
6165  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6166  SDValue SubVec = N->getOperand(1);
6167  SDValue InVec = N->getOperand(0);
6168 
6169  if (getTypeAction(SubVec.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector)
6170  SubVec = GetWidenedVector(SubVec);
6171 
6172  if (SubVec.getValueType().knownBitsLE(VT) && InVec.isUndef() &&
6173  N->getConstantOperandVal(2) == 0)
6174  return DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, SDLoc(N), VT, InVec, SubVec,
6175  N->getOperand(2));
6176 
6177  report_fatal_error("Don't know how to widen the operands for "
6178  "INSERT_SUBVECTOR");
6179 }

6193 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_STORE(SDNode *N) {
6194  // We have to widen the value, but we want only to store the original
6195  // vector type.
6196  StoreSDNode *ST = cast<StoreSDNode>(N);
6197 
6198  if (!ST->getMemoryVT().getScalarType().isByteSized())
6199  return TLI.scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG);
6200 
6201  if (ST->isTruncatingStore())
6202  return TLI.scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG);
6203 
6204  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> StChain;
6205  if (GenWidenVectorStores(StChain, ST)) {
6206  if (StChain.size() == 1)
6207  return StChain[0];
6208 
6209  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(ST), MVT::Other, StChain);
6210  }
6211 
6212  // Generate a vector-predicated store if it is custom/legal on the target.
6213  // To avoid possible recursion, only do this if the widened mask type is
6214  // legal.
6215  // FIXME: Not all targets may support EVL in VP_STORE. These will have been
6216  // removed from the IR by the ExpandVectorPredication pass but we're
6217  // reintroducing them here.
6218  SDValue StVal = ST->getValue();
6219  EVT StVT = StVal.getValueType();
6220  EVT WideVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), StVT);
6221  EVT WideMaskVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i1,
6222  WideVT.getVectorElementCount());
6223  if (WideVT.isScalableVector() &&
6224  TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::VP_STORE, WideVT) &&
6225  TLI.isTypeLegal(WideMaskVT)) {
6226  // Widen the value.
6227  SDLoc DL(N);
6228  StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6229  SDValue Mask = DAG.getAllOnesConstant(DL, WideMaskVT);
6230  MVT EVLVT = TLI.getVPExplicitVectorLengthTy();
6231  unsigned NumVTElts = StVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6232  SDValue EVL =
6233  DAG.getVScale(DL, EVLVT, APInt(EVLVT.getScalarSizeInBits(), NumVTElts));
6234  return DAG.getStoreVP(ST->getChain(), DL, StVal, ST->getBasePtr(),
6235  DAG.getUNDEF(ST->getBasePtr().getValueType()), Mask,
6236  EVL, StVal.getValueType(), ST->getMemOperand(),
6237  ST->getAddressingMode());
6238  }
6239 
6240  report_fatal_error("Unable to widen vector store");
6241 }
6242 
6243 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VP_STORE(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6244  assert((OpNo == 1 || OpNo == 3) &&
6245  "Can widen only data or mask operand of vp_store");
6246  VPStoreSDNode *ST = cast<VPStoreSDNode>(N);
6247  SDValue Mask = ST->getMask();
6248  SDValue StVal = ST->getValue();
6249  SDLoc dl(N);
6250 
6251  if (OpNo == 1) {
6252  // Widen the value.
6253  StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6254 
6255  // We only handle the case where the mask needs widening to an
6256  // identically-sized type as the vector inputs.
6257  assert(getTypeAction(Mask.getValueType()) ==
6258  TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6259  "Unable to widen VP store");
6260  Mask = GetWidenedVector(Mask);
6261  } else {
6262  Mask = GetWidenedVector(Mask);
6263 
6264  // We only handle the case where the stored value needs widening to an
6265  // identically-sized type as the mask.
6266  assert(getTypeAction(StVal.getValueType()) ==
6267  TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6268  "Unable to widen VP store");
6269  StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6270  }
6271 
6272  assert(Mask.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() ==
6273  StVal.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() &&
6274  "Mask and data vectors should have the same number of elements");
6275  return DAG.getStoreVP(ST->getChain(), dl, StVal, ST->getBasePtr(),
6276  ST->getOffset(), Mask, ST->getVectorLength(),
6277  ST->getMemoryVT(), ST->getMemOperand(),
6278  ST->getAddressingMode(), ST->isTruncatingStore(),
6279  ST->isCompressingStore());
6280 }

6282 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VP_STRIDED_STORE(SDNode *N,
6283  unsigned OpNo) {
6284  assert((OpNo == 1 || OpNo == 4) &&
6285  "Can widen only data or mask operand of vp_strided_store");

6287  SDValue Mask = SST->getMask();
6288  SDValue StVal = SST->getValue();

6291  if (OpNo == 1)

6295  else
6296  assert(getTypeAction(StVal.getValueType()) ==
6297  TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6298  "Unable to widen VP strided store");
6299 
6300  StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6301  Mask = GetWidenedVector(Mask);
6302 
6303  assert(StVal.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() ==
6304  Mask.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() &&
6305  "Data and mask vectors should have the same number of elements");

6308  SST->getChain(), DL, StVal, SST->getBasePtr(), SST->getOffset(),
6309  SST->getStride(), Mask, SST->getVectorLength(), SST->getMemoryVT(),

6311  SST->isCompressingStore());

6314 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_MSTORE(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6315  assert((OpNo == 1 || OpNo == 3) &&
6316  "Can widen only data or mask operand of mstore");
6317  MaskedStoreSDNode *MST = cast<MaskedStoreSDNode>(N);
6318  SDValue Mask = MST->getMask();
6319  EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType();
6320  SDValue StVal = MST->getValue();
6321  SDLoc dl(N);
6322 
6323  if (OpNo == 1) {
6324  // Widen the value.
6325  StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6326 
6327  // The mask should be widened as well.
6328  EVT WideVT = StVal.getValueType();
6329  EVT WideMaskVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6330  MaskVT.getVectorElementType(),
6331  WideVT.getVectorNumElements());
6332  Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
6333  } else {
6334  // Widen the mask.
6335  EVT WideMaskVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), MaskVT);
6336  Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
6337 
6338  EVT ValueVT = StVal.getValueType();
6339  EVT WideVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6340  ValueVT.getVectorElementType(),
6341  WideMaskVT.getVectorNumElements());
6342  StVal = ModifyToType(StVal, WideVT);
6343  }
6344 
6345  assert(Mask.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() ==
6346  StVal.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() &&
6347  "Mask and data vectors should have the same number of elements");
6348  return DAG.getMaskedStore(MST->getChain(), dl, StVal, MST->getBasePtr(),
6349  MST->getOffset(), Mask, MST->getMemoryVT(),
6350  MST->getMemOperand(), MST->getAddressingMode(),
6351  false, MST->isCompressingStore());
6352 }

6354 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_MGATHER(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6355  assert(OpNo == 4 && "Can widen only the index of mgather");
6356  auto *MG = cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N);
6357  SDValue DataOp = MG->getPassThru();
6358  SDValue Mask = MG->getMask();
6359  SDValue Scale = MG->getScale();
6360 
6361  // Just widen the index. It's allowed to have extra elements.
6362  SDValue Index = GetWidenedVector(MG->getIndex());
6363 
6364  SDLoc dl(N);
6365  SDValue Ops[] = {MG->getChain(), DataOp, Mask, MG->getBasePtr(), Index,
6366  Scale};
6367  SDValue Res = DAG.getMaskedGather(MG->getVTList(), MG->getMemoryVT(), dl, Ops,
6368  MG->getMemOperand(), MG->getIndexType(),
6369  MG->getExtensionType());
6370  ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
6371  ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res.getValue(0));
6372  return SDValue();

6375 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_MSCATTER(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6376  MaskedScatterSDNode *MSC = cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(N);
6377  SDValue DataOp = MSC->getValue();
6378  SDValue Mask = MSC->getMask();
6379  SDValue Index = MSC->getIndex();
6380  SDValue Scale = MSC->getScale();
6381  EVT WideMemVT = MSC->getMemoryVT();
6382 
6383  if (OpNo == 1) {
6384  DataOp = GetWidenedVector(DataOp);
6385  unsigned NumElts = DataOp.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
6386 
6387  // Widen index.
6388  EVT IndexVT = Index.getValueType();
6389  EVT WideIndexVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6390  IndexVT.getVectorElementType(), NumElts);
6391  Index = ModifyToType(Index, WideIndexVT);
6392 
6393  // The mask should be widened as well.
6394  EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType();
6395  EVT WideMaskVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6396  MaskVT.getVectorElementType(), NumElts);
6397  Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
6398 
6399  // Widen the MemoryType
6400  WideMemVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6401  MSC->getMemoryVT().getScalarType(), NumElts);
6402  } else if (OpNo == 4) {
6403  // Just widen the index. It's allowed to have extra elements.
6404  Index = GetWidenedVector(Index);
6405  } else
6406  llvm_unreachable("Can't widen this operand of mscatter");
6407 
6408  SDValue Ops[] = {MSC->getChain(), DataOp, Mask, MSC->getBasePtr(), Index,
6409  Scale};
6410  return DAG.getMaskedScatter(DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other), WideMemVT, SDLoc(N),
6411  Ops, MSC->getMemOperand(), MSC->getIndexType(),
6412  MSC->isTruncatingStore());
6413 }

6415 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VP_SCATTER(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {

6418  SDValue Mask = VPSC->getMask();
6419  SDValue Index = VPSC->getIndex();

6425  Index = GetWidenedVector(Index);
6426  const auto WideEC = DataOp.getValueType().getVectorElementCount();
6427  Mask = GetWidenedMask(Mask, WideEC);
6428  WideMemVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6429  VPSC->getMemoryVT().getScalarType(), WideEC);
6430  } else if (OpNo == 3) {
6431  // Just widen the index. It's allowed to have extra elements.
6432  Index = GetWidenedVector(Index);
6433  } else
6434  llvm_unreachable("Can't widen this operand of VP_SCATTER");

6438  VPSC->getVectorLength()};

6442 
6443 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
6444  SDValue InOp0 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6445  SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
6446  SDLoc dl(N);
6447  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6448 
6449  // WARNING: In this code we widen the compare instruction with garbage.
6450  // This garbage may contain denormal floats which may be slow. Is this a real
6451  // concern ? Should we zero the unused lanes if this is a float compare ?
6452 
6453  // Get a new SETCC node to compare the newly widened operands.
6454  // Only some of the compared elements are legal.
6455  EVT SVT = getSetCCResultType(InOp0.getValueType());
6456  // The result type is legal, if its vXi1, keep vXi1 for the new SETCC.
6457  if (VT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
6458  SVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i1,
6459  SVT.getVectorElementCount());
6460 
6461  SDValue WideSETCC = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, SDLoc(N),
6462  SVT, InOp0, InOp1, N->getOperand(2));
6463 
6464  // Extract the needed results from the result vector.
6465  EVT ResVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6466  SVT.getVectorElementType(),
6467  VT.getVectorElementCount());
6468  SDValue CC = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, ResVT, WideSETCC,
6469  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
6470 
6471  EVT OpVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
6472  ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
6473  TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT));
6474  return DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, dl, VT, CC);
6475 }
6476 
6477 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_STRICT_FSETCC(SDNode *N) {
6478  SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
6479  SDValue LHS = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
6480  SDValue RHS = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
6481  SDValue CC = N->getOperand(3);
6482  SDLoc dl(N);
6483 
6484  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6485  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
6486  EVT TmpEltVT = LHS.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
6487  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
6488 
6489  // Unroll into a build vector.
6490  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars(NumElts);
6491  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Chains(NumElts);
6492 
6493  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
6494  SDValue LHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, LHS,
6495  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
6496  SDValue RHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, RHS,
6497  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
6498 
6499  Scalars[i] = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, {MVT::i1, MVT::Other},
6500  {Chain, LHSElem, RHSElem, CC});
6501  Chains[i] = Scalars[i].getValue(1);
6502  Scalars[i] = DAG.getSelect(dl, EltVT, Scalars[i],
6503  DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, EltVT, VT),
6504  DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, EltVT, VT));
6505  }
6506 
6507  SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Chains);
6508  ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
6509 
6510  return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Scalars);
6511 }
6512 
6513 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE(SDNode *N) {
6514  SDLoc dl(N);
6515  SDValue Op = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6516  EVT OrigVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
6517  EVT WideVT = Op.getValueType();
6518  EVT ElemVT = OrigVT.getVectorElementType();
6519  SDNodeFlags Flags = N->getFlags();
6520 
6521  unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
6522  unsigned BaseOpc = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Opc);
6523  SDValue NeutralElem = DAG.getNeutralElement(BaseOpc, dl, ElemVT, Flags);
6524  assert(NeutralElem && "Neutral element must exist");
6525 
6526  // Pad the vector with the neutral element.
6527  unsigned OrigElts = OrigVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6528  unsigned WideElts = WideVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6529 
6530  if (WideVT.isScalableVector()) {
6531  unsigned GCD = std::gcd(OrigElts, WideElts);
6532  EVT SplatVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), ElemVT,
6533  ElementCount::getScalable(GCD));
6534  SDValue SplatNeutral = DAG.getSplatVector(SplatVT, dl, NeutralElem);
6535  for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx = Idx + GCD)
6536  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, dl, WideVT, Op, SplatNeutral,
6537  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
6538  return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Op, Flags);
6539  }
6540 
6541  for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx++)
6542  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, WideVT, Op, NeutralElem,
6543  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
6544 
6545  return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Op, Flags);
6546 }

6548 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE_SEQ(SDNode *N) {
6549  SDLoc dl(N);
6550  SDValue AccOp = N->getOperand(0);
6551  SDValue VecOp = N->getOperand(1);
6552  SDValue Op = GetWidenedVector(VecOp);
6553 
6554  EVT OrigVT = VecOp.getValueType();
6555  EVT WideVT = Op.getValueType();
6556  EVT ElemVT = OrigVT.getVectorElementType();
6557  SDNodeFlags Flags = N->getFlags();
6558 
6559  unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
6560  unsigned BaseOpc = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Opc);
6561  SDValue NeutralElem = DAG.getNeutralElement(BaseOpc, dl, ElemVT, Flags);
6562 
6563  // Pad the vector with the neutral element.
6564  unsigned OrigElts = OrigVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6565  unsigned WideElts = WideVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6566 
6567  if (WideVT.isScalableVector()) {
6568  unsigned GCD = std::gcd(OrigElts, WideElts);
6569  EVT SplatVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), ElemVT,
6570  ElementCount::getScalable(GCD));
6571  SDValue SplatNeutral = DAG.getSplatVector(SplatVT, dl, NeutralElem);
6572  for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx = Idx + GCD)
6573  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, dl, WideVT, Op, SplatNeutral,
6574  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
6575  return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), AccOp, Op, Flags);
6576  }
6577 
6578  for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx++)
6579  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, WideVT, Op, NeutralElem,
6580  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
6581 
6582  return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), AccOp, Op, Flags);
6583 }

6598 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VSELECT(SDNode *N) {
6599  // This only gets called in the case that the left and right inputs and
6600  // result are of a legal odd vector type, and the condition is illegal i1 of
6601  // the same odd width that needs widening.
6602  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6603  assert(VT.isVector() && !VT.isPow2VectorType() && isTypeLegal(VT));
6604 
6605  SDValue Cond = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6606  SDValue LeftIn = DAG.WidenVector(N->getOperand(1), SDLoc(N));
6607  SDValue RightIn = DAG.WidenVector(N->getOperand(2), SDLoc(N));
6608  SDLoc DL(N);
6609 
6610  SDValue Select = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, LeftIn.getValueType(), Cond,
6611  LeftIn, RightIn);
6612  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT, Select,
6613  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
6614 }
6615 
6616 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6617 // Vector Widening Utilities
6618 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6619 
6620 // Utility function to find the type to chop up a widen vector for load/store
6621 // TLI: Target lowering used to determine legal types.
6622 // Width: Width left need to load/store.
6623 // WidenVT: The widen vector type to load to/store from
6624 // Align: If 0, don't allow use of a wider type
6625 // WidenEx: If Align is not 0, the amount additional we can load/store from.
6626 
6627 static std::optional<EVT> findMemType(SelectionDAG &DAG,
6628  const TargetLowering &TLI, unsigned Width,
6629  EVT WidenVT, unsigned Align = 0,
6630  unsigned WidenEx = 0) {
6631  EVT WidenEltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
6632  const bool Scalable = WidenVT.isScalableVector();
6633  unsigned WidenWidth = WidenVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
6634  unsigned WidenEltWidth = WidenEltVT.getSizeInBits();
6635  unsigned AlignInBits = Align*8;
6636 
6637  // If we have one element to load/store, return it.
6638  EVT RetVT = WidenEltVT;
6639  if (!Scalable && Width == WidenEltWidth)
6640  return RetVT;
6641 
6642  // Don't bother looking for an integer type if the vector is scalable, skip
6643  // to vector types.
6644  if (!Scalable) {
6645  // See if there is larger legal integer than the element type to load/store.
6646  for (EVT MemVT : reverse(MVT::integer_valuetypes())) {
6647  unsigned MemVTWidth = MemVT.getSizeInBits();
6648  if (MemVT.getSizeInBits() <= WidenEltWidth)
6649  break;
6650  auto Action = TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), MemVT);
6651  if ((Action == TargetLowering::TypeLegal ||
6652  Action == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) &&
6653  (WidenWidth % MemVTWidth) == 0 &&
6654  isPowerOf2_32(WidenWidth / MemVTWidth) &&
6655  (MemVTWidth <= Width ||
6656  (Align!=0 && MemVTWidth<=AlignInBits && MemVTWidth<=Width+WidenEx))) {
6657  if (MemVTWidth == WidenWidth)
6658  return MemVT;
6659  RetVT = MemVT;
6660  break;
6661  }
6662  }
6663  }
6664 
6665  // See if there is a larger vector type to load/store that has the same vector
6666  // element type and is evenly divisible with the WidenVT.
6667  for (EVT MemVT : reverse(MVT::vector_valuetypes())) {
6668  // Skip vector MVTs which don't match the scalable property of WidenVT.
6669  if (Scalable != MemVT.isScalableVector())
6670  continue;
6671  unsigned MemVTWidth = MemVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
6672  auto Action = TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), MemVT);
6673  if ((Action == TargetLowering::TypeLegal ||
6674  Action == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) &&
6675  WidenEltVT == MemVT.getVectorElementType() &&
6676  (WidenWidth % MemVTWidth) == 0 &&
6677  isPowerOf2_32(WidenWidth / MemVTWidth) &&
6678  (MemVTWidth <= Width ||
6679  (Align!=0 && MemVTWidth<=AlignInBits && MemVTWidth<=Width+WidenEx))) {
6680  if (RetVT.getFixedSizeInBits() < MemVTWidth || MemVT == WidenVT)
6681  return MemVT;
6682  }
6683  }
6684 
6685  // Using element-wise loads and stores for widening operations is not
6686  // supported for scalable vectors
6687  if (Scalable)
6688  return std::nullopt;
6689 
6690  return RetVT;
6691 }
6692 
6693 // Builds a vector type from scalar loads
6694 // VecTy: Resulting Vector type
6695 // LDOps: Load operators to build a vector type
6696 // [Start,End) the list of loads to use.
6697 static SDValue BuildVectorFromScalar(SelectionDAG& DAG, EVT VecTy,
6698  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdOps,
6699  unsigned Start, unsigned End) {
6700  SDLoc dl(LdOps[Start]);
6701  EVT LdTy = LdOps[Start].getValueType();
6702  unsigned Width = VecTy.getSizeInBits();
6703  unsigned NumElts = Width / LdTy.getSizeInBits();
6704  EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), LdTy, NumElts);
6705 
6706  unsigned Idx = 1;
6707  SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, NewVecVT,LdOps[Start]);
6708 
6709  for (unsigned i = Start + 1; i != End; ++i) {
6710  EVT NewLdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
6711  if (NewLdTy != LdTy) {
6712  NumElts = Width / NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
6713  NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewLdTy, NumElts);
6714  VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVecVT, VecOp);
6715  // Readjust position and vector position based on new load type.
6716  Idx = Idx * LdTy.getSizeInBits() / NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
6717  LdTy = NewLdTy;
6718  }
6719  VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NewVecVT, VecOp, LdOps[i],
6720  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx++, dl));
6721  }
6722  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VecTy, VecOp);
6723 }
6724 
6725 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorLoads(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdChain,
6726  LoadSDNode *LD) {
6727  // The strategy assumes that we can efficiently load power-of-two widths.
6728  // The routine chops the vector into the largest vector loads with the same
6729  // element type or scalar loads and then recombines it to the widen vector
6730  // type.
6731  EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),LD->getValueType(0));
6732  EVT LdVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
6733  SDLoc dl(LD);
6734  assert(LdVT.isVector() && WidenVT.isVector());
6735  assert(LdVT.isScalableVector() == WidenVT.isScalableVector());
6736  assert(LdVT.getVectorElementType() == WidenVT.getVectorElementType());
6737 
6738  // Load information
6739  SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
6740  SDValue BasePtr = LD->getBasePtr();
6741  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
6742  AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
6743 
6744  TypeSize LdWidth = LdVT.getSizeInBits();
6745  TypeSize WidenWidth = WidenVT.getSizeInBits();
6746  TypeSize WidthDiff = WidenWidth - LdWidth;
6747  // Allow wider loads if they are sufficiently aligned to avoid memory faults
6748  // and if the original load is simple.
6749  unsigned LdAlign =
6750  (!LD->isSimple() || LdVT.isScalableVector()) ? 0 : LD->getAlign().value();
6751 
6752  // Find the vector type that can load from.
6753  std::optional<EVT> FirstVT =
6754  findMemType(DAG, TLI, LdWidth.getKnownMinValue(), WidenVT, LdAlign,
6755  WidthDiff.getKnownMinValue());
6756 
6757  if (!FirstVT)
6758  return SDValue();
6759 
6760  SmallVector<EVT, 8> MemVTs;
6761  TypeSize FirstVTWidth = FirstVT->getSizeInBits();
6762 
6763  // Unless we're able to load in one instruction we must work out how to load
6764  // the remainder.
6765  if (!TypeSize::isKnownLE(LdWidth, FirstVTWidth)) {
6766  std::optional<EVT> NewVT = FirstVT;
6767  TypeSize RemainingWidth = LdWidth;
6768  TypeSize NewVTWidth = FirstVTWidth;
6769  do {
6770  RemainingWidth -= NewVTWidth;
6771  if (TypeSize::isKnownLT(RemainingWidth, NewVTWidth)) {
6772  // The current type we are using is too large. Find a better size.
6773  NewVT = findMemType(DAG, TLI, RemainingWidth.getKnownMinValue(),
6774  WidenVT, LdAlign, WidthDiff.getKnownMinValue());
6775  if (!NewVT)
6776  return SDValue();
6777  NewVTWidth = NewVT->getSizeInBits();
6778  }
6779  MemVTs.push_back(*NewVT);
6780  } while (TypeSize::isKnownGT(RemainingWidth, NewVTWidth));
6781  }
6782 
6783  SDValue LdOp = DAG.getLoad(*FirstVT, dl, Chain, BasePtr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
6784  LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
6785  LdChain.push_back(LdOp.getValue(1));
6786 
6787  // Check if we can load the element with one instruction.
6788  if (MemVTs.empty()) {
6789  assert(TypeSize::isKnownLE(LdWidth, FirstVTWidth));
6790  if (!FirstVT->isVector()) {
6791  unsigned NumElts =
6792  WidenWidth.getFixedValue() / FirstVTWidth.getFixedValue();
6793  EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), *FirstVT, NumElts);
6794  SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, NewVecVT, LdOp);
6795  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, WidenVT, VecOp);
6796  }
6797  if (FirstVT == WidenVT)
6798  return LdOp;
6799 
6800  // TODO: We don't currently have any tests that exercise this code path.
6801  assert(WidenWidth.getFixedValue() % FirstVTWidth.getFixedValue() == 0);
6802  unsigned NumConcat =
6803  WidenWidth.getFixedValue() / FirstVTWidth.getFixedValue();
6804  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> ConcatOps(NumConcat);
6805  SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(*FirstVT);
6806  ConcatOps[0] = LdOp;
6807  for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumConcat; ++i)
6808  ConcatOps[i] = UndefVal;
6809  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, ConcatOps);
6810  }
6811 
6812  // Load vector by using multiple loads from largest vector to scalar.
6813  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> LdOps;
6814  LdOps.push_back(LdOp);
6815 
6816  uint64_t ScaledOffset = 0;
6817  MachinePointerInfo MPI = LD->getPointerInfo();
6818 
6819  // First incremement past the first load.
6820  IncrementPointer(cast<LoadSDNode>(LdOp), *FirstVT, MPI, BasePtr,
6821  &ScaledOffset);
6822 
6823  for (EVT MemVT : MemVTs) {
6824  Align NewAlign = ScaledOffset == 0
6825  ? LD->getOriginalAlign()
6826  : commonAlignment(LD->getAlign(), ScaledOffset);
6827  SDValue L =
6828  DAG.getLoad(MemVT, dl, Chain, BasePtr, MPI, NewAlign, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
6829 
6830  LdOps.push_back(L);
6831  LdChain.push_back(L.getValue(1));
6832  IncrementPointer(cast<LoadSDNode>(L), MemVT, MPI, BasePtr, &ScaledOffset);
6833  }
6834 
6835  // Build the vector from the load operations.
6836  unsigned End = LdOps.size();
6837  if (!LdOps[0].getValueType().isVector())
6838  // All the loads are scalar loads.
6839  return BuildVectorFromScalar(DAG, WidenVT, LdOps, 0, End);
6840 
6841  // If the load contains vectors, build the vector using concat vector.
6842  // All of the vectors used to load are power-of-2, and the scalar loads can be
6843  // combined to make a power-of-2 vector.
6844  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> ConcatOps(End);
6845  int i = End - 1;
6846  int Idx = End;
6847  EVT LdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
6848  // First, combine the scalar loads to a vector.
6849  if (!LdTy.isVector()) {
6850  for (--i; i >= 0; --i) {
6851  LdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
6852  if (LdTy.isVector())
6853  break;
6854  }
6855  ConcatOps[--Idx] = BuildVectorFromScalar(DAG, LdTy, LdOps, i + 1, End);
6856  }
6857 
6858  ConcatOps[--Idx] = LdOps[i];
6859  for (--i; i >= 0; --i) {
6860  EVT NewLdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
6861  if (NewLdTy != LdTy) {
6862  // Create a larger vector.
6863  TypeSize LdTySize = LdTy.getSizeInBits();
6864  TypeSize NewLdTySize = NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
6865  assert(NewLdTySize.isScalable() == LdTySize.isScalable() &&
6866  NewLdTySize.isKnownMultipleOf(LdTySize.getKnownMinValue()));
6867  unsigned NumOps =
6868  NewLdTySize.getKnownMinValue() / LdTySize.getKnownMinValue();
6869  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> WidenOps(NumOps);
6870  unsigned j = 0;
6871  for (; j != End-Idx; ++j)
6872  WidenOps[j] = ConcatOps[Idx+j];
6873  for (; j != NumOps; ++j)
6874  WidenOps[j] = DAG.getUNDEF(LdTy);
6875 
6876  ConcatOps[End-1] = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NewLdTy,
6877  WidenOps);
6878  Idx = End - 1;
6879  LdTy = NewLdTy;
6880  }
6881  ConcatOps[--Idx] = LdOps[i];
6882  }
6883 
6884  if (WidenWidth == LdTy.getSizeInBits() * (End - Idx))
6885  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT,
6886  ArrayRef(&ConcatOps[Idx], End - Idx));
6887 
6888  // We need to fill the rest with undefs to build the vector.
6889  unsigned NumOps =
6890  WidenWidth.getKnownMinValue() / LdTy.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
6891  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> WidenOps(NumOps);
6892  SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(LdTy);
6893  {
6894  unsigned i = 0;
6895  for (; i != End-Idx; ++i)
6896  WidenOps[i] = ConcatOps[Idx+i];
6897  for (; i != NumOps; ++i)
6898  WidenOps[i] = UndefVal;
6899  }
6900  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, WidenOps);
6901 }
6902 
6903 SDValue
6904 DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorExtLoads(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdChain,
6905  LoadSDNode *LD,
6906  ISD::LoadExtType ExtType) {
6907  // For extension loads, it may not be more efficient to chop up the vector
6908  // and then extend it. Instead, we unroll the load and build a new vector.
6909  EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),LD->getValueType(0));
6910  EVT LdVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
6911  SDLoc dl(LD);
6912  assert(LdVT.isVector() && WidenVT.isVector());
6913  assert(LdVT.isScalableVector() == WidenVT.isScalableVector());
6914 
6915  // Load information
6916  SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
6917  SDValue BasePtr = LD->getBasePtr();
6918  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
6919  AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
6920 
6921  if (LdVT.isScalableVector())
6922  report_fatal_error("Generating widen scalable extending vector loads is "
6923  "not yet supported");
6924 
6925  EVT EltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
6926  EVT LdEltVT = LdVT.getVectorElementType();
6927  unsigned NumElts = LdVT.getVectorNumElements();
6928 
6929  // Load each element and widen.
6930  unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
6931  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
6932  unsigned Increment = LdEltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
6933  Ops[0] =
6934  DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, EltVT, Chain, BasePtr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
6935  LdEltVT, LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
6936  LdChain.push_back(Ops[0].getValue(1));
6937  unsigned i = 0, Offset = Increment;
6938  for (i=1; i < NumElts; ++i, Offset += Increment) {
6939  SDValue NewBasePtr =
6940  DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, BasePtr, TypeSize::Fixed(Offset));
6941  Ops[i] = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, EltVT, Chain, NewBasePtr,
6942  LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), LdEltVT,
6943  LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
6944  LdChain.push_back(Ops[i].getValue(1));
6945  }
6946 
6947  // Fill the rest with undefs.
6948  SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
6949  for (; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
6950  Ops[i] = UndefVal;
6951 
6952  return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Ops);
6953 }
6954 
6955 bool DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorStores(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &StChain,
6956  StoreSDNode *ST) {
6957  // The strategy assumes that we can efficiently store power-of-two widths.
6958  // The routine chops the vector into the largest vector stores with the same
6959  // element type or scalar stores.
6960  SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
6961  SDValue BasePtr = ST->getBasePtr();
6962  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
6963  AAMDNodes AAInfo = ST->getAAInfo();
6964  SDValue ValOp = GetWidenedVector(ST->getValue());
6965  SDLoc dl(ST);
6966 
6967  EVT StVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
6968  TypeSize StWidth = StVT.getSizeInBits();
6969  EVT ValVT = ValOp.getValueType();
6970  TypeSize ValWidth = ValVT.getSizeInBits();
6971  EVT ValEltVT = ValVT.getVectorElementType();
6972  unsigned ValEltWidth = ValEltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
6973  assert(StVT.getVectorElementType() == ValEltVT);
6974  assert(StVT.isScalableVector() == ValVT.isScalableVector() &&
6975  "Mismatch between store and value types");
6976 
6977  int Idx = 0; // current index to store
6978 
6979  MachinePointerInfo MPI = ST->getPointerInfo();
6980  uint64_t ScaledOffset = 0;
6981 
6982  // A breakdown of how to widen this vector store. Each element of the vector
6983  // is a memory VT combined with the number of times it is to be stored to,
6984  // e,g., v5i32 -> {{v2i32,2},{i32,1}}
6985  SmallVector<std::pair<EVT, unsigned>, 4> MemVTs;
6986 
6987  while (StWidth.isNonZero()) {
6988  // Find the largest vector type we can store with.
6989  std::optional<EVT> NewVT =
6990  findMemType(DAG, TLI, StWidth.getKnownMinValue(), ValVT);
6991  if (!NewVT)
6992  return false;
6993  MemVTs.push_back({*NewVT, 0});
6994  TypeSize NewVTWidth = NewVT->getSizeInBits();
6995 
6996  do {
6997  StWidth -= NewVTWidth;
6998  MemVTs.back().second++;
6999  } while (StWidth.isNonZero() && TypeSize::isKnownGE(StWidth, NewVTWidth));
7000  }
7001 
7002  for (const auto &Pair : MemVTs) {
7003  EVT NewVT = Pair.first;
7004  unsigned Count = Pair.second;
7005  TypeSize NewVTWidth = NewVT.getSizeInBits();
7006 
7007  if (NewVT.isVector()) {
7008  unsigned NumVTElts = NewVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
7009  do {
7010  Align NewAlign = ScaledOffset == 0
7011  ? ST->getOriginalAlign()
7012  : commonAlignment(ST->getAlign(), ScaledOffset);
7013  SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NewVT, ValOp,
7014  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
7015  SDValue PartStore = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr, MPI, NewAlign,
7016  MMOFlags, AAInfo);
7017  StChain.push_back(PartStore);
7018 
7019  Idx += NumVTElts;
7020  IncrementPointer(cast<StoreSDNode>(PartStore), NewVT, MPI, BasePtr,
7021  &ScaledOffset);
7022  } while (--Count);
7023  } else {
7024  // Cast the vector to the scalar type we can store.
7025  unsigned NumElts = ValWidth.getFixedValue() / NewVTWidth.getFixedValue();
7026  EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewVT, NumElts);
7027  SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVecVT, ValOp);
7028  // Readjust index position based on new vector type.
7029  Idx = Idx * ValEltWidth / NewVTWidth.getFixedValue();
7030  do {
7031  SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NewVT, VecOp,
7032  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx++, dl));
7033  SDValue PartStore =
7034  DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr, MPI, ST->getOriginalAlign(),
7035  MMOFlags, AAInfo);
7036  StChain.push_back(PartStore);
7037 
7038  IncrementPointer(cast<StoreSDNode>(PartStore), NewVT, MPI, BasePtr);
7039  } while (--Count);
7040  // Restore index back to be relative to the original widen element type.
7041  Idx = Idx * NewVTWidth.getFixedValue() / ValEltWidth;
7042  }
7043  }
7044 
7045  return true;
7046 }
7047 
7048 /// Modifies a vector input (widen or narrows) to a vector of NVT. The
7049 /// input vector must have the same element type as NVT.
7050 /// FillWithZeroes specifies that the vector should be widened with zeroes.
7051 SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ModifyToType(SDValue InOp, EVT NVT,
7052  bool FillWithZeroes) {
7053  // Note that InOp might have been widened so it might already have
7054  // the right width or it might need be narrowed.
7055  EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
7056  assert(InVT.getVectorElementType() == NVT.getVectorElementType() &&
7057  "input and widen element type must match");
7058  assert(InVT.isScalableVector() == NVT.isScalableVector() &&
7059  "cannot modify scalable vectors in this way");
7060  SDLoc dl(InOp);
7061 
7062  // Check if InOp already has the right width.
7063  if (InVT == NVT)
7064  return InOp;
7065 
7066  ElementCount InEC = InVT.getVectorElementCount();
7067  ElementCount WidenEC = NVT.getVectorElementCount();
7068  if (WidenEC.hasKnownScalarFactor(InEC)) {
7069  unsigned NumConcat = WidenEC.getKnownScalarFactor(InEC);
7070  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumConcat);
7071  SDValue FillVal = FillWithZeroes ? DAG.getConstant(0, dl, InVT) :
7072  DAG.getUNDEF(InVT);
7073  Ops[0] = InOp;
7074  for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumConcat; ++i)
7075  Ops[i] = FillVal;
7076 
7077  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NVT, Ops);
7078  }
7079 
7080  if (InEC.hasKnownScalarFactor(WidenEC))
7081  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NVT, InOp,
7082  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
7083 
7084  assert(!InVT.isScalableVector() && !NVT.isScalableVector() &&
7085  "Scalable vectors should have been handled already.");
7086 
7087  unsigned InNumElts = InEC.getFixedValue();
7088  unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenEC.getFixedValue();
7089 
7090  // Fall back to extract and build (+ mask, if padding with zeros).
7091  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
7092  EVT EltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType();
7093  unsigned MinNumElts = std::min(WidenNumElts, InNumElts);
7094  unsigned Idx;
7095  for (Idx = 0; Idx < MinNumElts; ++Idx)
7096  Ops[Idx] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
7097  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
7098 
7099  SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
7100  for (; Idx < WidenNumElts; ++Idx)
7101  Ops[Idx] = UndefVal;
7102 
7103  SDValue Widened = DAG.getBuildVector(NVT, dl, Ops);
7104  if (!FillWithZeroes)
7105  return Widened;
7106 
7107  assert(NVT.isInteger() &&
7108  "We expect to never want to FillWithZeroes for non-integral types.");
7109 
7110  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> MaskOps;
7111  MaskOps.append(MinNumElts, DAG.getAllOnesConstant(dl, EltVT));
7112  MaskOps.append(WidenNumElts - MinNumElts, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, EltVT));
7113 
7114  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, NVT, Widened,
7115  DAG.getBuildVector(NVT, dl, MaskOps));
7116 }
